    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON EFA-12 - ADJUSTMENT - STEERING STOP ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>STEERING STOP ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0200603">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0200603" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200603.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. Steering Stop Adjustment</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to Steering General Service Information and Front Wheel Alignment, in GROUP 02 - FRONT
                AXLES in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual to determine correct steering stop angle.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check steering angle with alignment turntable set.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If adjustment is required, loosen jam nut and turn stop screw as necessary.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After adjustment, tighten stop screw nut to 90 - 120 ft-lbs. (122 - 163 N&#183;m).</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Adjust power steering unit so that power assist stops approximately 3&#176; or 1/8" (3.175 mm)
                        before reaching the steering stop screws.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
